The evidence with the title 'The high cost of resettling Middle Eastern refugees | center for ... ' says Nov 4, 2015  ... On average , each Middle Eastern refugee resettled in the United States costs an estimated $ 64,370 in the first five years, or $257,481 per household. The UN High Commissioner For Refugees ( UNHCR ) has requested $ 1,057 to care for each Syrian refugee annually in most countries neighboring Syria.
